review_blob: On tap at The Hop in Beacon NY. Pours a light Amber. Oranges, strawberry, wheat and fresh hop
On tap at the brewery. Crisp, full flavored pils, reminds me of pilsner urquell
On tap at Le Projet in Quebec city.. herbal, mellow, and dank. finishes bitter with fresh pine.
beer_name: Dunham / Kissmeyer Leos Early Breakfast IPA

review_blob: in Quebec city with Ellen at the brewpub tastes a lot like Hoegaarden. Delicious wit.
Excellent juicy ipa... reminds me of laguintas sucks a bit toned down.  try some.
On tap at the brewery.  Sweet floral, pine, tangerine upfront.. fresh and juicy.  Finish is bitter, but extremely well balanced. delicious ipa.. Could drink a lot of these.
Tall boy can enjoyed in Singapore.  Malty lager, medium bodied,  finishes dry and slightly bitter.
On tap at the brewpub with Jenny.  A lighter ipa... Dandelion and powder notes.  Refreshing, nice lacing.  Notes of fuggles hops
Draft at mugs.  Tangerine and sweet grain upfront, very sessionable... Usually not a big rye beer fan but this is an exception.

On tap at mugs ale house with Jenny.  Pour is dark, off white head, thick lacing.   Floral and herbal in the upfront taste.. Burnt caramelize malts in the finish coupled with bitter pine.  Great finish
beer_name: Evil Twin / Stillwater / Stone The Perfect Crime Black Smoked Saison

review_blob: Sample at the brewery with Jenny.  Sweet, syrupy oat taste.  Pours black with tan head.  Molasses and smokey earth notes.  Would like to see this barrel aged in bourbon
Sample at the brewery with Jenny.  Hot pinny aroma.. Very herbal in the nose but cuts to chocolate malts.  Taste isnt as full as the aroma.  Crisp hop pine bite, heat from booze, and chocolates.
Sample at the brewery with Jenny.  Tangy and dusty Saison... Sweet in the finish notes of hay.  Not overly dry.. Cloudy yellow
Bottle from the bottle shop in Philly. Shared w Phil.  Not much aroma... Taste is tangy malt, bitter.. Not a good taste overall.

On tap at Rattle n Hum with DNocks and Jredmond.   Nice fresh hop aroma, pours black with thin off white head.   Taste isnt as fresh as aroma but still nice a crisp well balanced black ipa... one of the best ive had.

At Le Germain hotel Toronto, can from the  mini bar.  Had a lot of recommendations to try this brewery out since its a stone throw from my hotel.. Glad I didnt because I was unsurprisingly unimpressed.  Had this after several pints of you unibroue chambly wit at Earls.  Has a crisp clean taste, a little dusty in the finish slight remnants of hay overall not bad. Its a little overhyped, somewhat like a medium bodied rolling rock beer.
Part of beer camp variety pack I got in Long Lake.  Tangy, fresh hop, upfront not overly floral but definitely juicy.   Finish shows more of the dandelion and citrus herbs.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp 053: Floral IPA

review_blob: On tap at the brewery w Moreau and James.  Roasty stout, sweet hops, chocolate and pine
On tap at the brewery w Moreau and James.  Sweet, floral.  Feels like its not entirely developed yet.. Watery.
On tap at the brewery w Moreau and James.  Juicy tangerine ipa, nicely balanced and a bitter floral finish. Great beer!
On tap at the brewery w Moreau and James.  Sweet, buttery pale ale, some nice citrus bitterness in the finish.  Highly drinkable
beer_name: Mountain Sun Paradise City Pale Ale

review_blob: On tap at the brewery w Moreau and James.  Strong, hefe notes, sugar dough.
beer_name: Mountain Sun Number One Belgian Trippel

review_blob: On tap at the brewery with James.  Sweet, soft, creamy Belgian ale. Apparently I had this 4 years ago.
On tap at Birreria at eataly with OConnell.  Nice sweet, grainy pale ale.  Rye and toast.

review_blob: Draft at Birreria with OConnell.  Buckwheat, orange, wheat, sweet finish and supple but could be better balanced.
Bottle at Breuklen Bier.  Sweet inky imperial stout.. Charcoal and toasted malt, finish with some caramel.

review_blob: Bottle purchased from whole foods Lincoln circle.  Split with Streetsie.  Hazy tan, orange brew with mild soapy white head.  Wheat, cream, light on the banana.  Its decent but by no means worth of 95 in style.
Bottle at Sapporo Ramen, NYC.  Not a bad beer.. Sweet cola, malt, and caramel.
At metropol in puerto Rico.  This beer is not good... Tastes like plastic and water
Bottle courtesy of Jenny.  Sweet and caramel characteristics... rich and supple oktoberfest.   Some body behind it, hazelnut and light cocoa.
bottle courtesy of Jennys monthly beer present.  Tart and sweet.. usualy hefe suspects in this one with some added lemon and florals.  Overall its light, refreshing, good wheat ale.
On tap at rattle and hum with James and Brendan.  Glad we were lucky enough to meet the brewer from perennial!  Delicious beer... Coconut, almond milk, and chocolates.  Macaroon in a glass
On tap at rattle with James and Brendan.  Dry ipa.. Bitter and rich.  Deep amber in color.  Finishes slightly boozey
On tap at rattle with James and Brendan.  Sweet and sour.. Nice tart guava and fruitiness

review_blob: On tap at rattle with James and Brendan.  Light esb, finishes flat. Some dusty notes, lemon, and light wheat.
beer_name: Kuhnhenn Timmy Ts English Pale Ale

review_blob: Draft at new york beer company.  Sweet and floral ipa.. Lemon peel, bitter hops, and tangy finish.
Bottle from city swiggers.  Malty, almost like a pale ale rather than ipa.  Good beer tho, would have again.
Tap at New York beer company. Last of the keg and free!  Pour is hazy yellow and frothy white. Soapy and little hefe tasting, decent
Bottle from city swiggers NYC.  Burnt caramel, crisp floral note, hay.  Crisp and refreshing.
On tap at pony bar.   Nice and balanced hefe... Not overly banan or clove where you get sick of it.  Sessionable wheat hefe brew.  Happy with this brew
On tap at pony bar.  Tobacco and some cottage cheese in the aroma.  Sweet malt ale. Ok
On cask at pony bar.  Nose is vinegary and piney.  Taste is pine, sweet, and astrigent.. Not good

review_blob: On tap at pony.  Malty and piney ipa.. Some orange tang in the finish. Dry, malty and sweet.
On tap at pony.  Really good for a kolsch but to be fair really tastes like a fresh citrusy ipa.  Great flavor, finishes light
On tap at pony bar.  Nutty brew.. Dry and some aluminum in the finish.  Style isnt my favorite to begin with but Its not good and I wouldnt order again

On tap at pony bar celebrating Brendans cfa passing.  Sweet and malty brew but also dusty and dry in the finish.. Somewhere allong the lines of a Belgian ale, brown ale and a triple.  Not overwhelming.. Tame.
Bottle from Trecolori with Feng and Tracy.  Soft, floral, and honey in the mouth... crisp and refreshing.
On tap at dieu di ciel w jenny. Hazy hefe color.. Tangy hop flare.  Grapefruit and heady topper reminders

review_blob: At the festival in Worcester Ma.  Ultra sweet tangerine, peach, orange, lemon, and cherry.  Sour and sweet.. Near perfection.

review_blob: Bottle at Gingermans w/ James after Tallest Man show.   Pleasantly surprised by this one - nice floral and herb scent.  Mouthfeel was smooth and crisp.. some more herbals, yeast
